CONTENT: Checklist
Turn off all lights.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: The slideout has two lights that must be manually switched off individually.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: The master bedroom has four lights that must be switched off individually. Two in the closets and two above the bed.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: The bunk house has six lights that must be switch off manually and individually.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: The bunk house has an Amazon echo that will work if connected to internet.
DESCRIPTION: There is a wifi range extender above the kitchen sink that you can connect too and it will connect to a nearby wifi network more effectively than a laptop. The Amazon Echo is connected to that.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: The slideout MUST not be used until the trailer is level or damage will be caused to the mechanism. It is extremely expensive to repair and would be reported as an insurance claim on your policy if damaged.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: Heater vents sometimes have things dropped in them, you may use the screwdriver to open them and get anything if necessary.
AUTHOR: Spencer (47554087)

CONTENT: Turn off the fans in the main room on the slideout wall are fans plugged into a USB outlet. Otherwise it will drain and damage the batteries.
